In tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/python/util/tf_should_use.py the function weakref.finalize is used. This is new since Python 3.4. Thus, it is not a distinction between Python 2 and Python 3 here. But clearly backports.weakrefshould not be a dependency for Python >= 3.4
Possible solution is to check if the finalize function exists in weakref module and import backports.weakref otherwise. Importing weakref should be safe, as it exists since Python 2.1:
import weakref
if not hasattr(weakref, 'finalize'):    
    from backports import weakref
Or alternatively
try:
    from weakref import finalize
except ImportError:
    from backports.weakref import finalize
as finalize is (currently) the only used member from weakref module in tf_should_use.
@mdeff Maybe you want to change the title of the issue to something like "Only use weakref.finalize from backports in Python < 3.4"
